38    /**
39    * Inlines functions that are divided into two types: "direct call node
40    * replacement" (aka "direct") and as a block of statements (aka block).
41    * Function that can be inlined "directly" functions consist of a single
42    * return statement, everything else is must be inlined as a "block". These
43    * functions must meet these general requirements:
44    * - it is not recursive
45    * - the function does not contain another function -- these may be
46    * intentional to to limit the scope of closures.
47    * - function is called only once OR the size of the inline function is smaller
48    * than the call itself.
49    * - the function name is not referenced in any other manner
50    *
51    * "directly" inlined functions must meet these additional requirements:
52    * - consists of a single return statement
53    *
54    */
